<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-08-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-08-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1267" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1267">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/8448.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Letcher</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-08-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 20, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your August 17. Instruct Agent, Parral, if rebels attempt to extort
                            forced loans from Americans to make unofficial and urgent protest
                            against such action and if protest unavailing, to instruct Americans in
                            question to pay under protest, making such protest a matter of record
                            and securing receipts if possible.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>